ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The tape worm mentioned here is commonly called the beef tapeworm or
_Taenia sagginata_. Well cooked meat does not present a risk to consumers.
However, it is important to realize that the infection requires that the
meat is eaten undercooked or raw. _Taenia sagginata_ is not
life-threatening and can easily be treated. This tape worm is present
worldwide and is not something as terrible as these articles make it out to
be. - Mods.EP/TG]
